steps.description:
Use one bead before each short half, and two beads before each long half. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/f2/Make-a-Snake-Puppet-Step-6Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Snake-Puppet-Step-6Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/f2/Make-a-Snake-Puppet-Step-6Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Snake-Puppet-Step-6Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Alternate "short" and "long" egg halves:{"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/ff/Make-a-Snake-Puppet-Step-6Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Snake-Puppet-Step-6Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/ff/Make-a-Snake-Puppet-Step-6Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Snake-Puppet-Step-6Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Here is the final body:{"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/4/4e/Make-a-Snake-Puppet-Step-6Bullet3.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Snake-Puppet-Step-6Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/4/4e/Make-a-Snake-Puppet-Step-6Bullet3.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Snake-Puppet-Step-6Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

String a few extra beads after the last egg half. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/2/2a/Make-a-Snake-Puppet-Step-7Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Snake-Puppet-Step-7Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/2/2a/Make-a-Snake-Puppet-Step-7Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Snake-Puppet-Step-7Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Tie off the last bead by tying the string to itself. Loop the string through the last bead once more for strength, and tie if off again. Trim the remaining string. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/0/0a/Make-a-Snake-Puppet-Step-7Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Snake-Puppet-Step-7Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/0/0a/Make-a-Snake-Puppet-Step-7Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Snake-Puppet-Step-7Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

To create rod A, drill a hole 1" (2.5cm) from each end of the dowel. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/e/e7/Make-a-Snake-Puppet-Step-8Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Snake-Puppet-Step-8Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/e/e7/Make-a-Snake-Puppet-Step-8Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Snake-Puppet-Step-8Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

To create rod B, drill a hole 1" (2.5cm) from each end as well as a third hole 1/2" (1.2cm) from one end. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/89/Make-a-Snake-Puppet-Step-8Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Snake-Puppet-Step-8Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/89/Make-a-Snake-Puppet-Step-8Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Snake-Puppet-Step-8Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Sand the splinters off with sandpaper, if necessary. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/f7/Make-a-Snake-Puppet-Step-8Bullet3.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Snake-Puppet-Step-8Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/f7/Make-a-Snake-Puppet-Step-8Bullet3.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Snake-Puppet-Step-8Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Line up the next control hole with the body, and tie a string as before to the body itself. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/d/d1/Make-a-Snake-Puppet-Step-12Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Snake-Puppet-Step-12Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/d/d1/Make-a-Snake-Puppet-Step-12Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Snake-Puppet-Step-12Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Before tying off the 2nd string, hold up the control and puppet to make sure that the 2nd string is the same length as the first. Tie the 2nd string to the control. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/b/ba/Make-a-Snake-Puppet-Step-12Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Snake-Puppet-Step-12Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/b/ba/Make-a-Snake-Puppet-Step-12Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Snake-Puppet-Step-12Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Repeat the process for the next two body strings and control rod B. Hold up the puppet every time to test the string length. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/e/e5/Make-a-Snake-Puppet-Step-12Bullet3.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Snake-Puppet-Step-12Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/e/e5/Make-a-Snake-Puppet-Step-12Bullet3.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Snake-Puppet-Step-12Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Be sure to connect the front-most body string to the inner hole of the front of rod B. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/ca/Make-a-Snake-Puppet-Step-12Bullet4.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Snake-Puppet-Step-12Bullet4.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/ca/Make-a-Snake-Puppet-Step-12Bullet4.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Snake-Puppet-Step-12Bullet4.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}
